{
  "stem": "3331.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Officially-- officially, they took to the army only people who were 21 years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I was 19 years.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I always was a very strong Polish patriot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I loved Poland.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even I knew Poland don't-- don't like me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I figured we are born in this country.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We live in this country.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Like when there was a holiday, a national holiday, all the children-- in school-- all the children walked with flags.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I always wanted to walk with a flag.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because this is my country.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- even my father was against it, I went.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Nobody knew about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I went, and I enlisted, and I said, I want to join the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the first day of the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Naturally, they didn't accept me, because they said, we don't have enough uniforms for our regular army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How will we have uniforms for you?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never told that to my parents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But right away, right away, parts of the army started to come through our town to come back, because we were not far from the border.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so they started to come back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, thousands and thousands of Jews from the border towns came through our town to run away to the east.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you could see, the army came back, but the civil people went away-- and mostly Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In our town, where it was 4,000 people, in the day of-- when the Germans entered our town, in our town there were 25,000 Jews from different towns.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody went through our town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was a reason why they went through our town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't have a railroad in our town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was a shortcut from a town, Tarnow, to the east, to Rzeszow, through the fields, to go through our town.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
